      "message": "The only reason it\u0027s done this way here (instead of just getting the top-level vbmeta struct via avb_slot_verify()) is because AvbSlotVerifyData (which is returned by avb_slot_verify() doesn\u0027t return the offset of where the top-level vbmeta partition is stored (this is needed to write the vbmeta top-level header after modifying it).\n\nSince fs_mgr doesn\u0027t have a need to write anything, you can just use avb_slot_verify() and you are guaranteed what AvbSlotVerifyData.vbmeta_images[0] is the top-level vbmeta header. So this is where you look in |flags| to determine if HASHTREE_DISABLED is set.\n\nI\u0027m still not sure what you are proposing to change in fs_mgr? (maybe continue the conversation in a CL for fs_mgr with what you\u0027re proposing to change.)",
